# Build context filter for the multi-stage Dockerfile.
#
# Anything matched here is NOT copied into the builder stage. Goal: keep
# build context small (faster `docker build`, less I/O over Railway's tar
# stream) and prevent local-only state from contaminating the image.
#
# This complements (not replaces) `outputFileTracingExcludes` in
# next.config.ts — that controls what `next build` traces; this controls
# what arrives at the build stage in the first place.

# Local install tree — Dockerfile runs `npm ci` fresh inside the builder.
node_modules

# Stale local Next builds — Dockerfile runs `next build` fresh.
.next

# Local SQLite DB, WAL files, recovery.jsonl. Production uses Railway
# Volume mount; nothing under data/ should ever ship.
data

# Zuzi's source paintings (her IP, see top-level .gitignore line 49).
# Already gitignored, but redundant defense.
samples/inputs

# Day-0 regression baselines — not needed at runtime; smoke runs are
# dev-only.
samples/day-0
samples/day-0-*

# Agent worktrees and any /tmp scratch.
.claude
tmp

# Backups
backups

# Env files. Secrets live in Railway env vars; .env.example documents the
# shape and is fine to ship if anyone wants it (but kept out for parity
# with .gitignore).
.env
.env.*

# Build / dev logs.
*.log
npm-debug.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# Git history — RAILWAY_GIT_COMMIT_SHA is passed as a build ARG, so the
# stamper doesn't need .git inside the container. Removing .git cuts a
# meaningful chunk of context size.
.git
.github

# Editor / OS noise.
.vscode
.idea
.DS_Store
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# Documentation isn't required at runtime.
README.md
docs

# The Dockerfile and .dockerignore themselves don't need to be inside
# the build context.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
